 The Ops PM manages all the Operations milestones across the Reliability, Product Engineering, Manufacturing Engineering and Planning team to ensure successful launch of a new product from Design release to Production release.
 What you'll be doing:
 The NPI PM role is responsible for coordinating and tracking operations deliverables for new systems from design through the production release phase.
 A strong PM candidate will co-ordinate program deliverables across planning, product engineering, manufacturing engineering teams to ensure the successful launch of our new servers.
 Responsible for updating the product bring-up status to the executive team and provide strategies to mitigate risk.
 Define the program management framework and tactics for successfully launching graphics-based server products from design/development/qualification/validation, through production release.
 Manage the supply chain and manufacturing plan of record for new products.
 Maintain project budgets and coordinate track procurement and delivery of bring-up hardware to facilitate the engineering teams.
 Ensuring System Baseboard/Server availability for internal and external customers during the NPI phase.
 Track reliability, qualification, product certification, and manufacturing readiness milestones across the engineering and CEM production teams.
 Align manufacturing and test POR assumptions and provide program management support for the initial production ramp plan.
 What we need to see:
 10+ years of experience in product management/production in server space.
 Excellent communication skills, ability to detail and present the current status and final project deliveries.
 Meaningful work experience in technical program, project, or product management role in the server space preferred.
 BS degree or equivalent experience in Electrical or Mechanical Engineering preferred.
 NVIDIA is leading the way in groundbreaking developments in Artificial Intelligence, High-Performance Computing and Visualization. The GPU, our invention, serves as the visual cortex of modern computers and is at the heart of our products and services. Our work opens up new universes to explore, enables outstanding creativity and discovery, and powers what were once science fiction inventions from artificial intelligence to autonomous cars. NVIDIA is looking for phenomenal people like you to help us accelerate the next wave of artificial intelligence.
